  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Part-time Exam Center Invigilator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>Studyworks provides examination and assessment services for clients in various industries. We administer exams such as the Halal Competency Assessment, UAPL Drone exam, CFA, Toefl, GRE and more.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will support exam administration by welcoming and checking in candidates, monitoring exam security, performing basic administrative tasks, and maintaining a clean and safe exam environment.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Greet candidates warmly and guide them through the check-in process to ensure a smooth start to exams</li><li>Conduct security checks on candidates to uphold exam integrity</li><li>Patrol and monitor candidates throughout the exam to prevent misconduct and ensure compliance with rules</li><li>Complete basic administrative tasks such as typing and filing daily reports accurately</li><li>Respond promptly and courteously to phone calls and enquiries related to exam procedures</li><li>Maintain cleanliness of the exam centre, including restrooms, by participating in scheduled housekeeping duties with the team</li><li>Follow all exam centre rules and regulations consistently to ensure a secure and fair testing environment</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum education level: O or N’ Level</li><li>Ability to work a minimum of 3 shifts per week, with each shift lasting 5 hours (e.g., 12:30 pm to 5:30 pm)</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Training will be provided to support your role</li></ul><p><strong>Pay</strong><br />$13 an hour plus CPF<br /><br /><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Working location: Tradehub 21, between Jurong East and Clementi</li></ul>",
